<br>
After zoning into Seb with no mana I decided to go AFK and do a couple of chores while I medded mana so I can go LFG and hopefully get 55.<br>
<br>
So I do this and after about 15 min I come back only to find myself back in the bazaar and with no gear/buffs and a loss of exp. Just then someone sends me a tell asking if I would like a rez and if I know what happend. Without giving it a second thought I took the rez and was back in Sebilis zone in doing what I thought I was supposed to be doing the last 15 min.<br>
<br>
About a min goes by and someone asks me if I could rez them... This made me wonder what they were thinking when I dont go /anon or /role ever. I do a /who all on him and it turns out to be a 56 druid in one of the *uber guilds* on my server. I told him that I could not rez him and after asking how he died he told me this.<br>
<br>
a_n00b_druid_057923 tells you, 'I was soloing and I went to the zone in to get some but no one would help me. Can you find me a rez?'<br>
<br>
I told him to hold tight as there were no rezzers near the zone in, needless to say I lied since there were at least 12 more people that were also dead. I asked my guild if anyone knew who he was. I got a tell from a guildie saying that he was now playing under a different name now because she met him a couple of moths ago asking for ports, sows, and even a PL when he was 52 even though he himself was a druid!! She also stated that he trained multiple groups on purpose to get camps and gates out of exp groups in emergancies instead of evacing the group letting everyone else die. And the list goes on and on so I wont get into horrible detail.<br>
<br>
As a result of this I told the druid I was trying to find him a rez and imediatly put him on ignore. The cleric that rezzed me said he was going to rez him but only after he had waited about 2 hours or more. Wise decision imo. I then proceeded to get a group and get back the exp that I lost and camped out in frustration thinking about it.<br>
<br>
But I guess in the end I wasnt too upset because I got my rez quickly and was on my way. But this I think this is going to become a major problem for people who have earned there keys into seb only to find themselves with a bunch of people who have not earned the right to be in seb in the first place imho.<br>
<br>
If you guys want me to I can leave his name here so you can all hopefully avoid yet another n00b, but for the time being I will leave it off because I think it is not proper. But you can always ask me in game hehe.<br>
<br>
Also for those who don't know, you cannot zone out of Seb the way you come in. One way exit and no turning back.<br>
<br>
post what you think, and do you think that VI/SoE will ever make the key a requirement again and/or will they remove the same requirement for HS and SS or other places of the sort.<br>
<br>
-Uprising<br>
54th Magician<br>
